      },
      {
        "step_no": 3,
        "text": "Whisk the lime crema by mixing mayonnaise, Greek yogurt, minced garlic, brown sugar, a pinch of salt and black pepper; adjust lime and seasoning to taste and set aside in fridge.",
        "time_min": 3
      },
      {
        "step_no": 4,
        "text": "Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat and add butter; when foaming, add pineapple chunks in a single layer and cook without moving until edges caramelize, about 2-3 minutes per side; remove and set aside.",
        "time_min": 6
      },
      {
        "step_no": 5,
        "text": "In the same skillet add olive oil and bring to high heat; add seasoned shrimp in a single layer and sear 1.5â€“2 minutes per side until opaque and slightly charred; finish with a squeeze of lime and reserve off heat.",
        "time_min": 4
      },
      {
        "step_no": 6,
        "text": "Warm tortillas on a dry skillet or directly over low gas flame until pliable and lightly charred, about 30 seconds per side; keep warm wrapped in a clean towel.",
        "time_min": 3
      },
      {
        "step_no": 7,
        "text": "Assemble tacos by placing a small handful of slaw on each tortilla, top with 3-4 shrimp, a few caramelized pineapple pieces, drizzle with lime crema, and garnish with sliced scallions and extra cilantro; serve immediately.",
